Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian 1 Abbotsford , BC Description Librarian 1 8889 Walnut Grove Dr, Langley Twp, BC V1M 2N7, Canada Req #76 Date closed: August 25, 2024 Job Type: Temporary, part time Affiliation: CUPE Location: Dean Drysdale Library Weekly Hours: 28 Schedule: Mon 8:30 am to 4:00 pm; Tues 12:30 pm to 8:00 pm; Wed 8:30 am to 4:00 pm; Thurs 8:30 am to 4:00 pm Job Start Date: September 3, 2024 Job End Date: March 3, 2025 Pay Grade: 11 Min Wage: 37.04 Max Wage: 43.24 THE POSITION: The Librarian 1 is responsible for the planning, supervision, organization and delivery of exceptional customer services. Plans, oversees and delivers library programs and events within the library, community, and virtually. This position is responsible for supervision and administrative duties. HERE IS WHAT YOU CAN BRING: Demonstrated proficiency in customer service skills. Demonstrated proficiency in leading a team in providing exceptional customer service. Ability to work independently and as part of a team. Strong interpersonal, oral and written communications skills. Demonstrated ability and skill to oversee and deliver a variety of creative programs: including the Playground, to all ages and abilities. This can be done both in-library and virtually. Adapts and embraces new methods of delivering programs and services based on customer needs. Demonstrated knowledge of and proficiency in readers’ advisory, reference search strategy/interview techniques and programming. In depth understanding of automated library systems and an ability to demonstrate a proficiency in the use of a variety of technologies. Demonstrated proficiency and interest in using a variety of related digital devices. Knowledge of public library resources and services. Ability to carry out job functions with flexibility, creativity and initiative. Strong organizational skills. Proficiency in Microsoft office POSITION REQUIREMENTS: Master's Degree in Library Science from an ALA accredited library school or equivalent library degree. Introductory supervisory training from a recognized institution, or equivalent to be completed within 6 months. Up to six months work related and on the job experience. Valid B.C. Driver's Licence (minimum level ‘N’). ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Criminal Record Check is required. Fraser Valley Regional Library is committed to maintaining a diverse and inclusive workplace and recognizes that a working environment that encourages input from all perspectives can only enhance our services to the public. We invite candidates who bring a diversity of thought, skills, and experiences to apply and thank you in advance for your interest and contributions.HOW TO APPLY:fvrl.bc.ca and go to Careers Compensation $37.04 to $43.24 per hour Closes: 25 August, 2024 Fraser Valley Regional Library Abbotsford , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
