Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager, Adult Services - Edmonton Public Library Edmonton , AB Description Job Number: 40504 Are you passionate about designing, delivering, and evaluating programming that support lifelong learning? Are you action-oriented with exceptional skills in leading, managing, and evaluating projects? Can you take on complex and interesting projects and lead teams from development through to execution?EPL is looking for an enthusiastic project-oriented leader to help shape and guide services for adults and ensure the delivery of exceptional experiences. Reporting to the Executive Director, Customer Experience, the Manager, Adult Services provides system-wide leadership of adult services and programming through oversight of EPL’s adult services’ teams and initiatives. The position is responsible for working with internal and external stakeholders to ensure high-quality, customer-centered activities are organized, executed, and evaluated. Diplomatic and collaborative with others, you are committed to establishing an environment of respect and accountability. The Manager, Adult Servies also oversees EPL’s Volunteer program, ensuring volunteer run programs are high quality and that a robust volunteer program is in place that supports the execution of exceptional customer experiences. Qualifications: Master of Library and Information Science degree from an ALA accredited library school.Seven years of progressively responsible professional library, leadership, supervisory, management or directly related experience, including a minimum of three years of leadership, supervisory, and management experience.Experience in community engagement and facilitation, and in program development, implementation and evaluation. Experience designing, developing, implementing, and evaluating programs and services.Knowledge of current trends in service design and development.Ability to work within a matrixed organizational environment managing projects and resources that cross organizational lines.Awareness of best practices and emerging issues and trends in online services and library applications of technology.Ability to adapt to continuously changing technology, and to assess and integrate best practices.Knowledge of STEAM technology including but not limited to 3D printing, application programming, Computer Assisted Design, Robotics and Electronics.Understanding of volunteer program development and management.Demonstrated superior interpersonal, communication, presentation, and collaboration skills.Ability to contribute positively and work effectively within a team environment. A commitment to excellent customer service.A commitment to upholding the Canadian Federation of Library Association's position statements on Intellectual Freedom and Diversity and Inclusion. What do you need to bring to this position? Experience designing, developing, implementing, and evaluating programs and services.Knowledge of current trends in service design and development.Ability to work within a matrixed organizational environment managing projects and resources that cross organizational lines.Awareness of best practices and emerging issues and trends in online services and library applications of technology.Ability to adapt to continuously changing technology, and to assess and integrate best practices.Knowledge of STEAM technology including but not limited to 3D printing, application programming, Computer Assisted Design, Robotics and Electronics.Understanding of volunteer program development and management.Demonstrated superior interpersonal, communication, presentation, and collaboration skills.Ability to contribute positively and work effectively within a team environment. A commitment to excellent customer service.A commitment to upholding the Canadian Federation of Library Association's position statements on Intellectual Freedom and Diversity and Inclusion. Note: Suitable candidates who do not meet the experience qualifications may be considered on a developmental basis. Satisfactory background screening is required for this position which includes a Criminal Record Check/Police Information check. Who we are: The secret ingredient for making EPL a magical place is no secret at all; in fact, it's very simple: We share. We share stories, ideas and experiences. We share with our customers, our communities, and ourselves. We are Edmonton's largest lender of all manner of information and entertainment. Hours of work: 35 hours per week Work Location(s): Stanley A. Milner Library, 7 Sir Winston Churchill Square, Edmonton T5J 2V4To apply: For more information about this position and other jobs available at the Edmonton Public Library, please visit www.epl.ca/careers and apply online. Only candidates who are selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $106,307 – $132,883 per annum Closes: 25 August, 2024 Edmonton Public Library Edmonton , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
