nd usage statistics on a regular and ad hoc basis to support decision-making and policy development by library management Liaise with personnel from Security, Library, Facilities and Business Operations departments, etc to ensure the security and maintenance of library facilities and equipment. C. Library Relations (25%) Represent the library's core values of accessibility, barrier free access to materials, EDI and commitment to Algoma University’s special mission. Ongoing commitment to maintain high quality library services for au students, faculty and staff with an concentrated effort to increase engagement with all academic divisions and community members.Connect and coordinate with multiple internal and external partners to promote library services and functional space. Identify and develop growth opportunities in order to fulfill Algoma University Library’s strategic planning goals. D. Other Duties (5%) Undertake other duties and responsibilities as assigned by the University Librarian.https://algomau.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Exte... Compensation $91,863 to $114,829 annually Closes: 21 August, 2024 Algoma University Sault Ste Marie , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
