Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager, Library Services Brampton , ON Description Algoma University is committed to undoing systemic and institutional discrimination and being publicly transparent and accountable. Diversity, equity, and inclusion are fundamental to our Special Mission. In keeping with the Seven Grandfather teachings that are the core values that inform our decisions as an institution, we are committed to creating a welcoming, inclusive, respectful, and safe environment where everyone belongs. We live these values through the strength and richness that diversity brings to our workforce and welcome contributors from equity-deserving groups including: Indigenous Peoples, Black and racialized persons, women, Persons with Disabilities, 2 Spirit, Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender, and Queer persons.Job Title:Manager, Library ServicesAdministrationPosition Status: Permanent, Full TimeNon-Union Department:Library Supervision Received:University LibrarianSupervision Exercised:Library Services Technician, Student Assistants Location:Brampton, ONNumber of Positions:1PRIMARY FUNCTIONS:A.Library Operations and Planning 40%B.Library Public Services 30%C.Library Relations 25%D.Other Duties 5%TOTAL 100%Reporting to the University Librarian, the Manager, Library services will provide support for both the University Librarian and Library Staff by assisting with leadership, training, handling library issues and finding solutions to support staff so they can provide the best services to students, faculty and community users.RESPONSIBILITIES:Library Operations and Planning (40%)Assist the University Librarian to provide leadership and direction to library staff in the development and delivery of library services.Contribute and support the University Librarian with visionary and strategic planning.Champion the implementation of progressive ideas to achieve goals through the development of competency based annual work plans.Provide mentorship to inspire staff for delivery of exemplary library services to all campus members.Lead library staff and working teams in the development and delivery of high quality services, programs, and collections responding to the needs of the community.Guide and coach staff to perform effectively and achieve performance measures.Keep abreast of trends and developments in the area of library management and recommend new and innovative approaches to enhance the performance of Algoma University Library.Assist the University Librarian to monitor and review the planning, management and control of revenues and expenditures to ensure fiscal accountability in the Library. Continual review of internal and external policies to ensure transparency and responsible operations. Prepare budget submissions; administer and monitor departmental operating budgets.Library Public Services (30%)Under the direction of the University Librarian, ensure the development, implementation of equitable policies and services in the provision of all in person and virtual services to Algoma University Library users.Keep abreast of developing technologies and monitor existing policies and procedures for efficiency and effectiveness. Identify and investigate new and changing needs for service and modify policies and procedures accordingly. Liaise with other university libraries’ personnel for general information. Collect and distribute circulation and usage statistics on a regular and ad hoc basis to support decision-making and policy development by library managementLiaise with personnel from Security, Library, Facilities and Business Operations departments, etc to ensure the security and maintenance of library facilities and equipment. Library Relations (25%)Represent the library's core values of accessibility, barrier free access to materials, EDI and commitment to Algoma University’s special mission.Ongoing commitment to maintain high quality library services for au students, faculty and staff with an concentrated effort to increase engagement with all academic divisions and community members.Connect and coordinate with multiple internal and external partners to promote library services and functional space.Identify and develop growth opportunities in order to fulfill Algoma University Library’s strategic planning goals.Other Duties (5%)Undertake other duties and responsibilities as assigned by the University Librarian.WORKING CONDITIONS: Physical Effort Minimal: Some lifting/physical effort required for transportation of materials.Physical EnvironmentMinimal:Minimal exposure to unpleasant/disagreeable conditions.Sensory AttentionConsiderable: Work requires a frequent need to concentrate on a variety of sensory inputs for a lengthy duration requiring diligence and attention (data gathering and analysis, attention to detail on reports for budgeting and strategic planning, etc.)Mental Stress Considerable: Work activities are performed in an environment with frequent exposure to mental pressures conditions where mental stress may be noticeable. Such as conflicting deadlines, dealing with angry/emotional disturbed/dangerous clients/public, shifting of work hours and travel.MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS
Master of Library &amp; Information Science with five (5) years of increasingly responsible experience in a university/academic or comparable institutional environment, ideally in a library/information setting.Demonstrate management and supervisory experience in a unionized environment.Excellent people management skills to direct and train staff in diverse functions and to handle sensitive personnel and patron situations. Ability to work with users and staff from diverse backgrounds and orientations. Proven ability to exercise initiative, good judgment and problem solving. Demonstrated ability to work independently and as part of a team. Knowledge of library systems and procedures. Excellent oral and written communication skills. Strong budget planning and control skills. Excellent organizational skills and the ability to set priorities, work under pressure and multi-task. Excellent planning, project management, and analytical skills. Demonstrated experience preparing reports and statistics. Intermediate knowledge of Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Access)and WordPress Knowledge of integrated library systems (ILSs) generally and of Alma/Primo (current ILS) specifically and library-related information technologies, applications and hardware would be an asset.Willingness to work non-regular hours.Ability to travel frequently between AlgomaU campuses.Salary Scale: $91,863 to $114,829 annually.To apply for this position please submit a resume and cover letter HERE no later than 4:00 p.m. on August 21, 2024.Algoma University is strongly committed to fostering diversity and inclusivity within our community and is an equal-opportunity employer. The university invites and encourages applications from all qualified individuals who would contribute to the further diversification of our Institution, including equity-deserving groups that are traditionally underrepresented in employment (Indigenous peoples, racialized persons, women, persons with disabilities, and 2SLGBTQQIPA+ persons). In accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act, 2005, upon request, accommodation will be provided by Algoma University throughout the recruitment, selection, and/or assessment process to applicants with disabilities. Compensation $91,863 to $114,829 annually Closes: 21 August, 2024 Algoma University Brampton , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
