Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Section Head Librarian 2 - Circulation Services Winnipeg , MB Description Recruitment DetailsSection Head Librarian 2 - Circulation Services Department: Library Services Designated Work Location: Millennium Library (1st Floor - 251 Donald Street) onsitePosition Type: Permanent, Full-timeSalary: $2,796.67 - $3,071.73 biweekly as per the Librarian 2 Classification (new rate of pay effective September 1, 2024)Posting No: 124881Closing Date: August 27, 2024Providing a wide range of services to over half of all Manitobans, The City of Winnipeg is one of the largest employers in Manitoba. We provide a comprehensive range of benefits and career opportunities to our employees. These include competitive salaries, employer-paid benefits, dental and vision care, pension plans, and maternity/parental leave programs. Additionally, we offer education, training, and staff development opportunities to ensure that our employees are equipped with the necessary skills to advance in their careers.Our Benefits web page provides detailed information about the benefits we offer, and we encourage you to visit it for further information at City of Winnipeg Benefits. We take pride in fostering a respectful, diverse, safe, and healthy workplace where our employees can thrive and achieve their full potential.The City is committed to attracting and retaining a diverse skilled workforce that is representative and reflective of the community we serve. Applications are encouraged from equity groups that have been and continue to be underrepresented at the City; Indigenous Peoples, Women, Racialized Peoples, Persons with Disabilities, 2SLGBTQQIA+ Peoples and Newcomers are encouraged to self-declare.Requests for Reasonable Accommodation will be accepted during the hiring process.Preference to internal applicants may be applied.Job Profile As Circulation Services Section Head Librarian, you are responsible for planning, developing, delivering and evaluating Circulation Services at Millennium Library. You supervise this high-traffic section and the services it provides to library customers including registering new borrowers, maintaining borrower records in the Library Services database, check-in/check-out services, shelving library materials, cash handling, and materials distribution across the system. You direct and evaluate the work of the staff in the section, organize and provide system-wide training, provide assistance in maintaining the library collection, create and maintain system-wide procedures; and handle complex escalated inquiries. As the Section Head Librarian you will:Plans, supervises and evaluates the operation of the Circulation Services Section at the Millennium Library and the delivery of its services, including the scheduling and delegation of work and regular meetings with section staff.Coordinates a variety of activities related to Circulation Services to ensure the provision of consistent and professional customer service throughout the Library system.Participates in the planning, implementation, and evaluation of new Circulation technologies and services at Millennium Library and throughout the Library system.Participates in the planning and development of public services at Millennium Library.Works with a variety of individuals and organizations to promote and enhance the section’s services.Provides and ensures the provision of responsive and inclusive customer service to children and adults.Provides leadership, direction, expertise and guidance to Circulation Services Section staff, as well as serves as a system resource for Circulation.Participates in the selection of the section’s circulation and shipping staff and ensures their training and evaluation.Provides expertise and guidance to system circulation staff to resolve difficult and non-routine circulation inquiries or problems.Ensures library circulation services training sessions are provided as needed.Ensures liaison with the Collection Agency to update and maintain the accuracy of individual system accounts.Responsible for ensuring the set up and operation of Millennium Library Book Sales.Prepares and ensures the preparation and or compilation of a variety of section and system reports and statistics.Participates in various system committees, co-chairs the Borrower Services Committee, and manages special projects as assigned.Performs other duties and assignments as required consistent with the classification.Your education and qualifications include:A Master of Library &amp; Information Sciences (MLIS) degree from an institution accredited by the American Library Association (ALA). An MLIS degree (or equivalent) obtained internationally through a formally accredited institution may also be considered.Demonstrated ability to provide excellent client-centered customer service.Demonstrated ability to plan and supervise the work of others and to work effectively as part of a team.Demonstrated knowledge of current and emerging technologies and their applications in libraries.Good knowledge of library Circulation systems, operations, and procedures.Demonstrated ability to analyze problems, develop and evaluate alternatives and recommend solutions.Ability to train staff in Circulation processes and the use of appropriate technology.Ability to work under stressful conditions and meet frequent, multiple and conflicting deadlines.Ability to make presentations and to promote library materials and services.Demonstrated ability to communicate effectively both orally and in writing with a variety of staff and customers.Ability to effectively promote the library and its services, programs and collections.Knowledge and understanding of the occupational hazards, safety precautions, regulations and procedures that are applicable to the area of work.Demonstrated ability to establish and maintain positive working relationships with employees at all levels of the organization, external contacts and the public, in accordance with the Respectful Workplace Policy.*IMPORTANT: Applicants who have been educated outside of Canada must have education which is comparable to the minimum qualification in Canada. Applicants submitting foreign credentials require an official academic assessment report issued by a recognized Canadian assessment service https://www.canalliance.org/en/ at application. Conditions of employment:The successful candidate must maintain legal eligibility to work in Canada. If the successful candidate possesses a work permit, it is their responsibility to ensure the permit remains valid.A Police Information Check satisfactory to the employer will be required from the successful candidate, at their expense. To obtain Police Information Check information please visit www.winnipeg.ca/police.Must be physically capable of performing the duties of the position (i.e., Must be able to lift boxes and equipment weighing 20-25 pounds)Must be available to work evenings and weekends. The successful applicant will be required to complete job specific training required for this position as directed. How to ApplyAPPLY ONLINE, including all documentation listed below:Current resume and cover letter (Required). Applications submitted without REQUIRED documentation will not be considered.*Your application documents must clearly indicate how you meet the qualifications of the position.*NotesOnline applications can be submitted at http://www.winnipeg.ca/hr/. For instructions on how to apply and how to attach required documents please refer to our FAQ's or contact 311. Hours of Work: Various (evenings and weekends required) Employee Group: C.U.P.E. Position Reports To: Administrative Coordinator of Central Library Services Only candidates selected for interviews will be contacted. Compensation $2,796.67 - $3,071.73 biweekly as per the Librarian 2 Classification (new rate of pay effective September 1, 2024) Closes: 27 August, 2024 Winnipeg Public Library Winnipeg , MB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
