tion with the CEO, uses the library branding to promote programs and events through various media outlets Maintains, publishes and submits related records, statistics and evaluations as required Utilize programming and outreach activities to promote additional programs, services and collections Tracks revenues and expenditures within the allocated programming budget in coordination with the CEO Other duties as required Skills &amp; Competencies Effective written and oral communication skillsDisplays excellent interpersonal and team-oriented workplace skillsWorking knowledge of ILS systems, Microsoft Office software, social media platforms, CanvaAptitude for organization with attention to detail and accuracy; maintains confidentialityExperience in a public service setting, preferably in a public library environmentAbility to establish and maintain effective working relationships with community groups, external agencies and the general public. Excellent communication, organizational and interpersonal skillsRelevant undergraduate degree or approved equivalent combination of education and experience; public library experience is an assetValid Driver’s License (class G)2 years of proven excellence in programming and outreach including customer serviceExperience working with children Ability to multi-task on a daily basis Qualifications Working Relationships: Internal Library Staff, CEO, Municipal Staff External Library Patrons, Community Partners, Local Elementary Schools Working Conditions Constant interaction with the general public Evening and weekend service desk/program shifts required Requires travel within the community Position requires lifting – 20lbs+ ; shoveling snow Physical demand requires a high positive energy level, computer usage, sitting, standing, bending, and lifting Working conditions are conducted in a library environment, also includes conditions outside the library environment in various community settings, with exposure to public interaction, questions and concerns Multi-tasking is required on a daily basis At times works alone evening, weekends and occasionally midweek. Please send cover letter and resume to Amanda Robinson at ceo@lanarklibrary.ca by August 23, 2024 at noon. Compensation $26.93-$31.69 (2024 rates) Closes: 23 August, 2024 Lanark Highlands Public Library Lanark , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
